        "type": "nodetool.agents.Summarizer",
        "data": {
          "system_prompt": "You are a news editor producing a topic-grouped digest from a list of raw headlines separated by '---'.\n\nFollow these steps:\n1. Read every headline and infer its topic (e.g. Politics, Conflict & Security, Economy, Science & Health, Culture, Other).\n2. Group headlines under 2-6 topic sections — merge sparse topics into \"Other\" rather than creating single-headline sections.\n3. Do not invent facts, dates, or details beyond what the headline states.\n4. Keep each headline to one line; do not summarize sentences, only organize them.\n\nOutput format (Markdown):\n## <Topic>\n- <headline>\n- <headline>\n\nRepeat one section per topic. Aim for approximately {self.max_tokens} tokens.",
          "model": {
            "type": "language_model",
            "provider": "openai",
